<br>
Just curious, not that I expect everyone to reply, but I wonder if anyone actually knows what this is all about or are the people joining in the attack just because they want to?  On a RP standpoint.  Defending it's another matter as those will and are varied.  But the real reason for the attack?  One maybe two or three differences on why. <p><BR>Jarroo Dooger<BR>Tinker's Pride<BR>Gnome Cleric of Bristlebane<BR>"...we are our brothers keeper, that we have an obligation to look out for one another.  If we're bound and determined to seek our own destruction nothing can stop that... but anything less, and a kind word in the right place, an action taken at the right time, can bend history and help others." - J. Michael Straczynski</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upentapod.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pentapod</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.ozemail.com.au/~pentapod/graphics/a_pod.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>WTB phat newt</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/25/02 10:59:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=273.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When Angels Cried..........7/30 Event</span><hr size=1> As a defender, I don't really care why Apep is attacking ... I'm bound to defend Ak'Anon because I believe the attack is wrong.  But I gather there was some controversy over Apep and Charizma's marriage, and Apep believes that some gnomes have caused pain to his wife, and this is some sort of retaliation for that?  Stories which possibly also involve Kuladen in some way?  Certainly I know the Tinker's Pride were rather torn over Charizma's decision, and also that Charizma is unaware this assault is planned.  Would like to know more if there's some handy links ... ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaroodooger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaroo Dooger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/26/02 12:42:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=273.topic&index=72>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When Angels Cried..........7/30 Event</span><hr size=1> I'm afraid that any links I could give you are a bit scattered or just plain nonexcistant (sp), but you do have the general idea.  It is a heated topic.  One which I've found myself getting more heated than I would normally do.  Talk about beating a dead horse but some will not let it go.  And no Apep that was not in any way refering to you, Ebon Storm, or Charizma.  (Just in case. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )Take a trip over to the Tinker's Pride message board.  Lurk around a bit and you'll more than likely find out what's going on (for the most part at least)  The remaining members of the guild have pretty much put it behind them and are ready or getting ready for the attack.  We are more than ready to pick up the pieces afterwards and hope the reconstruction of Ak'Anon doesn't take too long.  That is... if any part does get destroyed. <p><BR>Jarroo Dooger<BR>Tinker's Pride<BR>Gnome Cleric of Bristlebane<BR>"...we are our brothers keeper, that we have an obligation to look out for one another.  If we're bound and determined to seek our own destruction nothing can stop that... but anything less, and a kind word in the right place, an action taken at the right time, can bend history and help others." - J. Michael Straczynski</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxianya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xianya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/26/02 1:17:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=273.topic&index=73>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When Angels Cried..........7/30 Event</span><hr size=1> This raid has been called to right a wrong against a person. I have no idea if Baron Apep knows who actually caused the wrongs but I do know he intends to make all gnomekind pay for it. He has also informed me he intends to keep it as a free-for-all. This means, according to pnp, he has the right to walk into Ak'Anon and slay any npc defender he comes across at will. I am in my 43rd season and 90% of the defenders con blue to me.<br>
<br>
Is this justice? Does it make for a good raid? All I know is the ONLY ways to oppose him would be to duel. And there is no guarentee any of them would accept. You condemn us for attempting to summon the  Lag. I condemn you for considering this to be a fair two-sided event. You say we should attack Neriak in retaliation. Who is the more heathen of us? I walk the darkened streets of Neriak because some of my friends call it home. There is no justice here. Only a megalomaniacs ego in full bloom.<br>
<br>
So condemn us for standing in his way and trying to stop him. He can come and destroy us at any time when we are unprepared, If you doubt me, see for yourself just how weak the Ak'Anon defenders really are. You will find less than 20 inhabitants in the whole city who can even hold a candle to one such as Baron Apep. Ask Baron Gore how easy it was when he came unannounced. The entity known as Verant has stood idly by, not acknowledging the one-sidedness of this event. Their suggestion is that we all see our local Priest of Discord and sign up to be Pvp Players for just a day? Ask anyone who has been pvp on a nonpvp server how hard it was for them to get changed back.<br>
<br>
We even asked if we could have Byg Benn (the clockwork dragon) released in order to defend, but again, Verant denies us.<br>
<br>
And if Baron Apep declines to appear for the raid at the time of his choosing, it will show cowardice on his part. He is commited and we expect him to stand by his word, lest it become worthless.Apep has said that it was up to the individual on how they choose to fight. And I think many would choose NOT to fight those of us who stand at the gates because they would rather have the easier prey behind us.<br>
<br>
It boggles the mind how so many can rally to his cause solely to cause death without any rewards, save for a rusty sword or a piece of scrap metal. Possibly for even a few rare silver coin, a defender's life savings.<br>
<br>
So to hell with your condemnation of our defense of Ak'Anon. You are in OUR world now.<br>
<br>
Xianya Lilboomer<br>
